Wow! I was just doing more research on this very subject!<br>
<br>
I have to agree with torn prince and midnight vampiress on this one.  I had a similar experience with a being who calls himself Azrael... and although muslim literature names him an angel of death, he was a very human jewish priest.  The study became so intense and there was so much material to share I ended up putting it on a website.<br>
<br>
Spiritual contact affects us each in deeply personal ways... but we do have to be careful of our own ghosts.  Religious programming, political propaganda and personal perceptions of the same, sometimes have us name something before we've even asked a question.  Thats why spiritual communication can often be a maddening experience... it's hard to tell what's real, when current realities are challenged.<br>
<br>
If it's an experience you can't seem to get past or let go, you might want to open a dialogue by asking questions and just wait out the answers... they come out eventually. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/udrakewick.showPublicProfile?language=EN>drakewick</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(5/18/02 9:24:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: the angel of death</span><hr size=1> one question I propose to all is how do you all know what the angel of death looks likes? I mean when you die you die that it. So do you really know what he or she or it looks like? So please let me know. Thank you  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/usadshadows.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sad Shadows</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 98<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(5/18/02 3:01:00 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: angel of death</span><hr size=1> azrael9<br>
