Sparkles <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/uazrael9.showPublicProfile?language=EN>azrael9</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(6/17/02 7:00:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: angel of death</span><hr size=1> Hi,<br>
<br>
You write: &quot;A spirit claiming to be an angel isn't that uncommon.&quot;<br>
<br>
snip<br>
<br>
What is even funnier though is when an spirit is mistaken for an angel<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/emoticons_classic/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Such is the case with Azrael... and Jesus Christ for that matter.  Did you know they were both written as the son of God?  Both were ressurected from the dead to become a &quot;sign unto their people&quot;.  This type of fiction was a popular theme for the time... a reality the church does not want anyone to know... so they hid away all the stories that named other religious leaders.<br>
<br>
It took me quite awhile to get my hands on the piece that transformed Ezra (human priest and scribe) to Azra-el, son of God (bene Elohim).  I finally got hold of it through the Muslims.<br>
<br>
But, yes, I do laugh when I see angels portrayed in the pop-gear... wings and harps or now, black robes and scythes!  The funniest of problems I've encountered during my research was a dispute over the naming of angels.  The other laughable problem is transliteration of names.  For instance, do you know that Azra, Ezra, Esdras, Uzayr, and Ophelia are all the same word (Hebrew: help) and that adding the &quot;el&quot; to the end of one's name was just the Hebrews way of establishing the equivilent of the Christian's version of sainthood?<br>
<br>
But the one most important thing to remember is that these religions were insecure amongst eachother... and were competing heavily for public audience.  Just keep that in mind when next you read about the parting of the red sea or death riding upon his horse to apocalypse and all that... they are no different than your grandfather's fishing tales!  Doesn't mean dear ol' grandad never went fishing... but it does imply that he may not have caught a whale<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/emoticons_classic/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Besides, life is far too short to get caught up in the politics of competing religions and much like watergate... it all comes out in the end.  This business about heirarchies and offices wreaks too much of current politics and I wonder how people don't see the resemblance?<br>
<br>
Anyway... just my humble input<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/emoticons_classic/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Sheila9<br>
