 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/bunexplainedmysteries.showUserPublicProfile?gid=azrael9>azrael9</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/2/02 3:45:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: DEATH, GRIM REAPER, ETC ETC</span><hr size=1> Hi Westside Mike,<br>
<br>
I've just checked that out (fortunately Google lets us have pages translated).<br>
<br>
I don't think it's surprizing that LA SANTISIMA MUERTE emulates the Medieval Christian platform considering that LA SANTISIMA MUERTE was adopted with it.<br>
<br>
In other words, LA SANTISIMA MUERTE is not their own - it does not pre-date their conversion to Christianity.  It was an influence of it.<br>
<br>
It's amazing!  The study I'm conducting.  I am told by so many people that they are aware of, and not prone to, political manipulation, religious programming and commercial marketting, and yet, despite this assurance, I find many people &quot;under the influence&quot; of these methods.<br>
<br>
When I was a child, I used to love an old fable called &quot;The Emporer's New Clothes&quot;.  In this story, a deceitful tailor convinced a king that he was wearing special clothing that could only be seen by people of intelligence.  The word spread throughout the kingdom and because no one wanted to be discovered as stupid, everyone went along with it!  All but one child, who cried out in the procession:  &quot;Look!  The King has no clothes!&quot;<br>
<br>
I would like to believe what is convenient.  That we don't have to be responsible people, we can mess things up as much as we want, because a &quot;hero&quot; will come one day and put everything right for us.  But I don't buy the convenience of that thought - and it's a crime... the messes our ancestor's left for us to deal with.<br>
<br>
I have traced the story of Azrael and found what I expected.  A simple man who made a bold move to better his people.  His name and identity have been stolen to promote the ends of others, so many times over, it's sickening!  Fortunately they have kept their records!<br>
<br>
Those records explain why intermarriage was not allowed (how this story became corrupted to the level of angels mating with women... God only knows)!  It reads quite clearly:  &quot;Now,  after these things were done, the princes came to me  <br>
saying; The people of Israel,  and the priests, and Levites have not separated themselves from the people of the lands, doing according to their abominations,  of the Canaanites, the Hittites, the Perizzites, the Jebusites, the Ammonites, the Moabites, the Egyptians, and the Amorites.  For they have taken of their daughters for themselves, and for their sons, so their holy seed have mingled themselves with the people of the lands:  yea, the hand of the princes and rulers hath been chief in this trespass.&quot;<br>
<br>
The &quot;holy seed&quot; was contained in men!  The story I read about the fallen angels came 500 years later.  The part about angels having wings came in the 10th century ad, because one artist was inspired by a statue of the Greek Goddess Nike.<br>
<br>
Today, Nike is a sneaker and angels are seen everywhere wearing wings.  At a rate of just a penny a head per buyer, boy would that look good on a spread-sheet!<br>
<br>
Selling fairy tales is easy!  I mean just check out the herd instinct.  But it may pay to check out the whole story!  So Azrael gathered the dust for the creation of adam and therefore was made the angel of death.  Even the encyclopedias will tell you that!<br>
<br>
What they won't tell you is that the story was written by the same (12th century ad) author with two entirely different outcomes.  In version one, Azrael fails and God had to get the earth himself.  In the next version Azrael succeeds and is made the angel of death.<br>
<br>
Why two different outcomes?  Because the original version was written by a Christian heretic named Marcion in the year 97 ad.  He wanted the early christian church to turn away from the Jews and is responsible for the division in testaments (old and new).  He believed that an evil angel was responsible for the creation of mankind and that the angel was hostile to God.<br>
<br>
Plagiarism at best describes the work that followed.  The Tales from Masnavi which details the two versions of the story.  Azrael had to fail in the version that was presented to convert the Christians, because they were familiar with Marcion's verdict.  But Azrael could be useful in a story that was intended to convert a Jewish audience.<br>
<br>
It's all politics and the power of numbers.  Every group had a &quot;testimonials&quot; page to sell their concept (just like most advertisements) and no testimony was more valuable than one who had converted.  A repsectable Christian or Jew, who converted to Islam was a priceless win.  And vice-versa... three ways!<br>
<br>
As these religions compete for the global title, they will tell you anything, promise you anything... and if that doesn't work they will threaten you.  So, you have to ask yourself, while starring in the eye of the dragon... what will you do?  Admire the King's new clothes like good cattle?<br>
<br>
Story time is over... and a new world awaits.  Are you ready?<br>
<br>
